The paper discusses the development of a memetic algorithm for optimization problems, which falls under the category of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of local search heuristics, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the algorithm to a suite of optimization problems, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of stochastic adaptation rules could also fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper mentions the 2012 IEEE Congress on Evolutionary Computation, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
